I cannot believe how nasty `URI.resolve()` really is its full of nasty edge cases.

    new URI(&quot;http://localhost:80&quot;).resolve(&quot;foo&quot;) =&gt; &quot;http://localhost:80foo&quot;
    new URI(&quot;http://localhost:80&quot;).resolve(&quot;//foo&quot;) =&gt; &quot;http://foo&quot;
