For including the branch name in version: 

Use a variable in your `&lt;version&gt;` value:

    &lt;version&gt;${branch}-SNAPSHOT&lt;/version&gt;

Then in your ci script, run maven with arguments:

    ./mvnw -Dbranch=${CI_COMMIT_BRANCH} clean install/package/deploy/etc

You may need to use different [predefined CI variables][1] depending on whether a tag or branch was pushed (or if it was a merge request event etc.)

You can put a sensible default in your pom.xml&#39;s properties section

    &lt;properties&gt;
        &lt;branch&gt;local&lt;/branch&gt;
    &lt;/properties&gt;

This will be used if no value is provided when building.


  [1]: https://docs.gitlab.com/ee/ci/variables/predefined_variables.html

